  "summary": "Line divides the screen",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "Every time I wake up from sleeping in bed, there is a line in the middle of the screen similar to a beacon. If I move, it disappears. n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Create a new Survival world with default settings.\n2. Locate or craft a bed and place it in an area with at least two blocks of vertical space above it.\n3. Ensure that it is nighttime in the game.\n4. Right-click or interact with the bed to sleep in it.\n5. Wait for the screen to fade to black and for the time to skip to dawn.\n6. Upon waking up, observe the screen for the appearance of a vertical line dividing it, similar to a beacon.\n7. Move the character around to confirm that the line disappears when in motion.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 1.21.8",
  "Observed Behavior": "Upon waking up from sleeping in a bed, a prominent horizontal line appears across the center of the player's screen, resembling the visual effect of a beacon beam. This line is persistent until the player moves their character, at which point the line disappears. The issue occurs consistently every time the player wakes up from sleep, regardless of the bed's location or the game mode being used. The line does not affect gameplay mechanics but can be visually distracting. This behavior has been observed in both single-player and multiplayer modes. No other visual anomalies have been reported in conjunction with this issue, suggesting it is isolated to the waking-up process from bed.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When a player wakes up from sleeping in a bed, the screen should transition smoothly without displaying any unintended visual artifacts, such as a line dividing the screen. The player should experience a clear view of their surroundings immediately upon waking, without any graphical glitches. If there are any issues with the screen display, such as lines or flickering, they should not occur, and the game should function normally, allowing the player to move freely without any visual disturbances.",
